lab
===

Personal Linux systems toolbox. Learning experiment, also running in production
at home. Reads from /proc directly - no wrappers, no abstractions over
abstractions.

Tools
-----

  cktop    - terminal UI for system monitoring
  ckstat   - one-shot CLI, prints current memory usage
  ckagent  - metrics agent, exposes /proc data in Prometheus exposition format
  ckapi    - HTTP behavior simulator (delay, CPU burn, memory pressure, fail injection)


cktop
-----

  go install github.com/ckinan/lab/cmd/cktop@latest


ckstat
------

  go install github.com/ckinan/lab/cmd/ckstat@latest

  ckstat          # human-readable
  ckstat -o json  # JSON


ckagent
-------

  go install github.com/ckinan/lab/cmd/ckagent@latest

  ckagent                  # listens on :9110
  ckagent -addr :9111      # custom port

Metrics at http://localhost:9110/metrics. Scrape with VictoriaMetrics or
Prometheus. Systemd unit and alert rules in deploy/.

Metrics exposed:

  cpu, memory, swap, load averages
  per-core CPU usage
  disk I/O (reads, writes, io time)
  network (bytes, packets, drops, errors per interface)
  open file descriptors
  socket counts (tcp, udp, raw, orphan, timewait)
  vmstat (page faults, paging, swapping)
  process/task counts
  system uptime
  apt last update and last upgrade timestamps
  PSI - pressure stall information (cpu, memory, io) system-wide and per-service
  per-service: CPU %, RSS, process count, PSI (via cgroups)


ckapi
-----

  cd ckapi && go install ./cmd

  ckapi                    # listens on :9120
  ckapi -addr :9121        # custom port

Programmable HTTP target. Set default behavior via /control, override
per-request via /work. Designed to drive real metrics into VictoriaMetrics
and Grafana using k6 for load generation (see k6/).

Endpoints:

  POST /work      execute a behavior (delay, cpu burn, memory, fail injection)
  POST /control   set default behavior for subsequent /work requests
  GET  /control   read current defaults
  GET  /metrics   Prometheus exposition (ckapi_* + go_memstats_*)
  GET  /health    liveness check

Request fields (all optional, inherit from /control defaults if omitted):

  delay_ms       integer   sleep N ms before responding
  cpu_burn_ms    integer   spin the CPU for N ms
  mem_use_bytes  integer   allocate N bytes
  mem_hold       bool      hold allocation for the duration of the request
  fail           bool      return 500 (or status_code if set)
  status_code    integer   return specific HTTP status code

Example:

  # set defaults: 50ms delay, 10% fail rate
  curl -s -X POST localhost:9120/control \
    -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
    -d '{"delay_ms":50,"fail":false}'

  # override for a single request: 800ms delay
  curl -s -X POST localhost:9120/work \
    -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
    -d '{"delay_ms":800}'

Grafana dashboard in deploy/grafana/ckload.json. Systemd unit in
deploy/ckapi.service.


k6 load generation
------------------

Continuous synthetic load against ckapi. Requires k6 (k6.io).

  k6 run k6/ckapi.js                            # run locally
  CKAPI_URL=http://host:9120/work k6 run k6/ckapi.js  # custom target

Scenarios in k6/ckapi.js:

  steady          30 RPS constant, 20ms delay
  latency-spike   20 RPS base, spikes to 150 RPS with 800ms delay every 5m
  sawtooth-load   5-100 RPS sawtooth, 50ms delay
  error-injection 10 RPS constant, fail=true
  memory-hold     5 RPS constant, 10MB held per request

Each scenario runs for 24h. Run as a systemd service (Restart=always) for
continuous load. Systemd unit in deploy/ckload.service.

  task install:load  # install k6 script + systemd service


Development
-----------

Requires Go 1.21+ and Task (taskfile.dev).

  task build          # build all binaries
  task test           # unit tests
  task run:agent      # run ckagent locally
  task run:api        # run ckapi locally
  task run:load       # run k6 locally (requires k6)
  task install:agent  # build and deploy ckagent to /usr/local/bin + restart systemd
  task install:api    # build and deploy ckapi to /usr/local/bin + restart systemd
  task install:load   # deploy k6 script + restart systemd service

